snippet.textDisplay:
There are very few songs that can pierce through your heart.
This song was released on Buddha Purnima. The most special day for the Buddhist community. You guys might have already figured out that Coke Studio Bangla has targeted the festival/special days mostly celebrated in Bangladesh to release its songs. This song depicted one's eternal longing for his/her loved ones, waiting, and the bittersweet feelings of it. Probably it also reminds us of the pain and longing of Gautam Buddha's wife Yashodhara (Joshodhora in Bengali) when He left His home to know about life's greater meaning. But nobody talked about the wife who was left behind.
